  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Blackboard architecture is a coordination pattern where multiple specialist agents share a common data structure \u2014 the blackboard \u2014 instead of communicating through direct message passing. Each agent reads whatever data it needs from the blackboard, performs its analysis, and writes its results back. A controller (or LangGraph edges) decides which agent runs next based on the current blackboard state."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Blackboard coordination architecture: multiple agents read and write a central shared state",
          "title": "Blackboard Architecture"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Core Data Structures"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The blackboard is a typed state dictionary. Every field uses either a last-write-wins assignment or a reducer-annotated list so parallel agent writes merge safely:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import operator\nfrom typing import Annotated, Any\nfrom typing_extensions import TypedDict\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass Finding:\n    agent_id: str\n    claim: str\n    confidence: float\n    evidence: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n\n\nclass BlackboardState(TypedDict):\n    # Reducer-annotated \u2014 parallel agents can append safely\n    findings: Annotated[list[Finding], operator.add]\n    hypotheses: Annotated[list[str], operator.add]\n    critiques: Annotated[list[str], operator.add]\n\n    # Last-write-wins scalars\n    control_flags: dict[str, Any]   # e.g. {\"stop\": True, \"focus\": \"security\"}\n    final_report: str               # written once by the reporter agent\n    iteration: int                  # monotonically incremented by controller"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Using ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Annotated[list, operator.add]",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for list fields means LangGraph concatenates all parallel writes. A field without an annotation is last-write-wins \u2014 the final state update seen by the runtime wins."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Building the Blackboard Graph"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each specialist is a regular LangGraph node. The controller inspects the blackboard and returns the next node name:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from langgraph.graph import StateGraph, END\nfrom langchain_anthropic import ChatAnthropic\n\nresearcher_llm = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\")\ncritic_llm = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\")\nsynthesizer_llm = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-sonnet-5\")\n\n\ndef researcher(state: BlackboardState) -> dict:\n    prompt = f\"Iteration {state['iteration']}. Produce 3 findings on the topic. Focus: {state['control_flags'].get('focus', 'all')}\"\n    response = researcher_llm.invoke(prompt)\n    findings = _parse_findings(\"researcher\", response.content)\n    return {\"findings\": findings, \"iteration\": state[\"iteration\"] + 1}\n\n\ndef critic(state: BlackboardState) -> dict:\n    claims = \"\\n\".join(f.claim for f in state[\"findings\"][-3:])\n    response = critic_llm.invoke(f\"Critique these claims:\\n{claims}\")\n    return {\"critiques\": [response.content]}\n\n\ndef synthesizer(state: BlackboardState) -> dict:\n    all_claims = \"\\n\".join(f.claim for f in state[\"findings\"])\n    all_critiques = \"\\n\".join(state[\"critiques\"])\n    response = synthesizer_llm.invoke(\n        f\"Synthesize findings into hypotheses:\\n{all_claims}\\n\\nCritiques:\\n{all_critiques}\"\n    )\n    return {\"hypotheses\": [response.content]}\n\n\ndef controller(state: BlackboardState) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Route based on current blackboard state.\"\"\"\n    flags = state[\"control_flags\"]\n    if flags.get(\"stop\"):\n        return \"reporter\"\n    if len(state[\"findings\"]) < 6:\n        return \"researcher\"\n    if len(state[\"critiques\"]) < len(state[\"findings\"]) // 3:\n        return \"critic\"\n    if not state[\"hypotheses\"]:\n        return \"synthesizer\"\n    return \"reporter\"\n\n\ndef reporter(state: BlackboardState) -> dict:\n    report_lines = [\"# Analysis Report\", \"\"]\n    for h in state[\"hypotheses\"]:\n        report_lines.append(f\"## Hypothesis\\n{h}\\n\")\n    report_lines.append(f\"Total findings: {len(state['findings'])}\")\n    return {\"final_report\": \"\\n\".join(report_lines)}\n\n\nbuilder = StateGraph(BlackboardState)\nbuilder.add_node(\"researcher\", researcher)\nbuilder.add_node(\"critic\", critic)\nbuilder.add_node(\"synthesizer\", synthesizer)\nbuilder.add_node(\"reporter\", reporter)\n\nbuilder.set_entry_point(\"researcher\")\nbuilder.add_conditional_edges(\"researcher\", controller)\nbuilder.add_conditional_edges(\"critic\", controller)\nbuilder.add_conditional_edges(\"synthesizer\", controller)\nbuilder.add_edge(\"reporter\", END)\n\ngraph = builder.compile()"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "controller",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " function acts as the blackboard's control loop: it reads the current state and determines which specialist should run next. This replaces the fixed pipeline sequence with data-driven routing."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Running the Graph"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "initial_state: BlackboardState = {\n    \"findings\": [],\n    \"hypotheses\": [],\n    \"critiques\": [],\n    \"control_flags\": {\"focus\": \"security vulnerabilities\"},\n    \"final_report\": \"\",\n    \"iteration\": 0,\n}\n\nresult = graph.invoke(initial_state)\nprint(result[\"final_report\"])\nprint(f\"Total findings collected: {len(result['findings'])}\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Parallel Knowledge Sources with Send"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When multiple researcher agents should run simultaneously, use the ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Send",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " API to fan out. All their findings merge into the blackboard via ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "operator.add",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ":"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from langgraph.types import Send\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass ResearchTask:\n    domain: str\n    depth: str\n\n\ndef make_specialist(domain: str):\n    \"\"\"Factory: returns a node function bound to a domain.\"\"\"\n    llm = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\")\n\n    def specialist(task: ResearchTask) -> dict:\n        response = llm.invoke(f\"Research {domain} at depth '{task.depth}'.\")\n        findings = [\n            Finding(agent_id=f\"specialist_{domain}\", claim=response.content,\n                    confidence=0.85, evidence=[domain])\n        ]\n        return {\"findings\": findings}\n\n    return specialist\n\n\ndef dispatcher(state: BlackboardState) -> list[Send]:\n    \"\"\"Fan out one Send per research domain.\"\"\"\n    domains = [\"security\", \"performance\", \"usability\", \"compliance\"]\n    depth = state[\"control_flags\"].get(\"depth\", \"shallow\")\n    return [\n        Send(f\"specialist_{d}\", ResearchTask(domain=d, depth=depth))\n        for d in domains\n    ]\n\n\n# Register one node per specialist\nfor domain in [\"security\", \"performance\", \"usability\", \"compliance\"]:\n    builder.add_node(f\"specialist_{domain}\", make_specialist(domain))\n\nbuilder.add_conditional_edges(\"dispatcher\", dispatcher)\n# After all specialists finish, route to critic\nfor domain in [\"security\", \"performance\", \"usability\", \"compliance\"]:\n    builder.add_edge(f\"specialist_{domain}\", \"critic\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LangGraph waits for all four ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Send",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " targets to finish before merging their outputs. The blackboard's ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "findings",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " list accumulates all four domain results automatically through the ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "operator.add",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " reducer."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Dynamic Control via Flags"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The blackboard's ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "control_flags",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " field lets one agent influence the routing of subsequent agents without tight coupling. A planner agent writes flags; the controller reads them:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def planner(state: BlackboardState) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Inspect hypothesis quality; set flags to direct next steps.\"\"\"\n    if not state[\"hypotheses\"]:\n        return {\"control_flags\": {**state[\"control_flags\"], \"needs_more_research\": True}}\n\n    low_confidence = [\n        f for f in state[\"findings\"] if f.confidence < 0.6\n    ]\n    if len(low_confidence) > len(state[\"findings\"]) * 0.4:\n        # Too many low-confidence findings \u2014 direct researcher to dig deeper\n        return {\n            \"control_flags\": {\n                **state[\"control_flags\"],\n                \"depth\": \"deep\",\n                \"focus\": \"evidence quality\",\n            }\n        }\n\n    if len(state[\"hypotheses\"]) >= 3:\n        # Enough hypotheses \u2014 stop iteration\n        return {\"control_flags\": {**state[\"control_flags\"], \"stop\": True}}\n\n    return {\"control_flags\": state[\"control_flags\"]}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Flags are plain dict values, so any agent can inspect them with a dict ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ".get()",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " call. This avoids coupling agents to each other \u2014 the planner never calls the researcher directly."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Confidence-Weighted Finding Aggregation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rather than treating all findings equally, a custom reducer can merge findings by confidence score. Replace the default ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "operator.add",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " with a function:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def merge_findings(existing: list[Finding], new: list[Finding]) -> list[Finding]:\n    \"\"\"Merge keeping highest-confidence finding per (agent_id, claim) pair.\"\"\"\n    combined = {(f.agent_id, f.claim): f for f in existing}\n    for f in new:\n        key = (f.agent_id, f.claim)\n        if key not in combined or f.confidence > combined[key].confidence:\n            combined[key] = f\n    # Sort descending by confidence\n    return sorted(combined.values(), key=lambda f: f.confidence, reverse=True)\n\n\nclass BlackboardStateV2(TypedDict):\n    findings: Annotated[list[Finding], merge_findings]   # custom reducer\n    hypotheses: Annotated[list[str], operator.add]\n    critiques: Annotated[list[str], operator.add]\n    control_flags: dict[str, Any]\n    final_report: str\n    iteration: int"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A custom reducer receives ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(existing_value, new_value)",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and returns the merged result. This is the correct place to implement deduplication, scoring, or eviction logic \u2014 it runs inside LangGraph's state merge step, not in a node."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Persisting the Blackboard Across Sessions"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Use ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "SqliteSaver",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " or ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "MemorySaver",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to checkpoint the blackboard so a long-running analysis can be interrupted and resumed. The thread ID acts as the blackboard's unique identity:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from langgraph.checkpoint.sqlite import SqliteSaver\n\nwith SqliteSaver.from_conn_string(\"blackboard.db\") as checkpointer:\n    graph = builder.compile(checkpointer=checkpointer)\n\n    config = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"analysis-project-42\"}}\n\n    # First run: begin analysis\n    state = graph.invoke(initial_state, config=config)\n    print(f\"Checkpoint after run 1: {len(state['findings'])} findings\")\n\n    # Second run: resume \u2014 blackboard state is loaded from SQLite\n    # Inject fresh control flags without re-running from scratch\n    graph.update_state(config, {\"control_flags\": {\"focus\": \"performance\", \"stop\": False}})\n    state2 = graph.invoke(None, config=config)  # None = resume from checkpoint\n    print(f\"After resumption: {len(state2['findings'])} findings\")"
          }
        ]
      },
